I"ç<p>Suppose $p$ has no zeros on a curve $C$. Then,</p>

<script type="math/tex; mode=display">\int_C\frac{p'(z)}{p(z)} dz = i\arg(p(z))|_C.</script>

<p>The number of zeros is given by</p>

<script type="math/tex; mode=display">N = \frac{1}{2\pi i}\int_C\frac{p'}{p} dz.</script>

<p>This evaluates to</p>

<script type="math/tex; mode=display">N = \frac{1}{2\pi}(n\pi + 2\arg p|_\Gamma)</script>

